This paper discusses a system for managing the storage and reuse of intermediate results in MapReduce workflows, which is a topic related to data management and distributed systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of high-level query languages such as Pig, Hive, and Jaql, which are related to programming languages and compilers, suggesting cs.PL (Programming Languages) as another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the system as an extension to the Pig dataflow system on top of Hadoop, which is related to software engineering, suggesting cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on the PigMix benchmark, which is related to data structures and algorithms, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category.
